{
  "description": "A close-up photograph showcases a vibrant orange tulip in partial bloom. The flower is angled downwards, with its petals gracefully unfurling. The petals exhibit a gradient of color, transitioning from a deep orange-red at the top to a softer, almost pastel orange towards the base. Hints of yellow are visible at the very tips of the petals. The background is a deep, blurred black, enhancing the contrast and drawing focus to the tulip. Soft light highlights the delicate textures of the petals, creating subtle shadows and a sense of depth. There is a glimpse of a green stem or another part of the plant in the blurred background, but it is out of focus. ",
